.Dd May 23, 2000
.Dt LFS_SEGCLEAN 2
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm lfs_segclean
.Nd mark a segment clean
.Sh LIBRARY
.Lb libc
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Fd #include \*[Lt]sys/types.h\*[Gt]
.Ft int
.Fn lfs_segclean "fsid_t *fsidp" "u_long segment"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Fn lfs_segclean
marks segment number
.Fa segment
in LFS filesystem
.Fa *fsidp
"clean" or available for writing.
.Sh RETURN VALUES
.Fn lfs_segclean
returns 0 on success, or -1 on error.
.Sh ERRORS
An error return from
.Fn lfs_segclean
indicates:
.Bl -tag -width Er
.It Bq Er EFAULT
.Fa fsidp
points outside the process's allocated address space.
.It Bq Er EINVAL
.Fa *fsidp
does not specify a valid filesystem.
.It Bq Er EBUSY
.Fa segment
is marked SU_ACTIVE, meaning that it does not yet belong to a valid checkpoint.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr lfs_bmapv 2 ,
.Xr lfs_markv 2 ,
.Xr lfs_segwait 2 ,
.Xr lfs_cleanerd 8
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Fn lfs_segclean
function call appeared in
.Bx 4.4 .
